#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code count karta hai kitne substrings me at least ek 'a', ek 'b' aur ek 'c' present ho.

1. hash array me a, b, c ka latest index store karte hain.
2. String ko left se right traverse karte hain.
3. Har character ka latest index update kar dete hain.
4. Jab teeno characters kam se kam ek baar mil jaate hain,
   to unke latest indices me se jo minimum hoga,
   us tak ke sab starting positions valid hongi.
5. Isliye count me add karte hain:
   1 + min(lastIndexOfA, lastIndexOfB, lastIndexOfC)

Main idea:
Agar current index i tak a, b, c teeno mil gaye,
to earliest valid start 0 se lekar minimum latest index tak ho sakta hai.
Isliye utne saare substrings current i par end hote hue valid ban jaate hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int numberOfSubstrings(String s) {
        int n = s.length();
        int[] hash = new int[3];
        Arrays.fill(hash, -1);
        int cnt = 0;

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            hash[s.charAt(i) - 'a'] = i;

            if(hash[0] != -1 && hash[1] != -1 && hash[2] != -1){
                cnt += 1 + Math.min(hash[0], Math.min(hash[1], hash[2]));
            }
        }
        return cnt;
        
    }
}
